summary: This document is an email chain from November 2021 discussing a proffer agreement, with an attached FBI 302 interview report. It involves communication between an Assistant United States Attorney and members of the NYPD/FBI Child Exploitation Human Trafficking Task Force regarding obtaining a signed proffer agreement from a client.

events.title: Proffer Agreement Draft Sent
events.description: An Assistant United States Attorney sends the most recent version of a proffer agreement to attorney EL, requesting it be initialed by EL and their client.

events.title: Request for Interview Notes and 302
events.description: A request is made for interview notes and the FBI 302 report related to the proffer agreement process.

events.title: Notes Provided, 302 Pending
events.description: Interview notes are provided, with the FBI 302 report to be sent once it is signed off.

events.title: 302 Report Attached
events.description: The FBI 302 interview report is attached to an email from the NYPD/FBI Child Exploitation Human Trafficking Task Force.

keyFacts: The document is an email chain concerning a proffer agreement in a child exploitation and human trafficking investigation.
An FBI 302 interview report is attached to the correspondence, indicating an interview related to the case was conducted.
The communication involves the NYPD/FBI Child Exploitation Human Trafficking Task Force and an Assistant United States Attorney.
The emails show a back-and-forth process to finalize a proffer agreement with a client represented by attorney EL.
